                        <head>187. Summary of Conclusions of a Special Coordination Committee
                                Meeting<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d187fn1">Source: National
                                Security Council, <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName>
                                Administration Intelligence Files, Box I020, Minutes-<gloss target="#t_SCC_1">SCC</gloss> 1979. Secret. The meeting took
                                place in the White House Situation Room. The minutes are not
                                attached and were not found. <persName corresp="#p_DC_1">Dodson</persName> sent the Summary of Conclusions to <persName corresp="#p_MWF_1">Mondale</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_VCR_1">Vance</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_BH_2">Brown</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_JDC_1">Jones</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_TS_1">Turner</persName>
                                under a March 19 memorandum signed by Carolyn Cleveland (<gloss target="#t_NSC_1">NSC</gloss>).</note>
                        </head>
